Another ingredient that we have neglected in our considerations so far is the
explicit chiral symmetry breaking term , arising through the
current quark masses. A term linear in  does not appear expicitly
in the evolution equations, as the flow equation ()
involves second functional derivatives of the action with respect to the
fields. For this reason the linear term can be added directly to the
potential at any scale. 







The phase diagram for  

Let us summarize the main points of the framework we have set up.
Our theory is defined through the potential of eq. ()
at a scale . 
In a realistic theory we can identify  with the
